HEADWORD: Bovate
<hw>Bo"vate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>bovata</ets>, fr. <ets>bos</ets>, <ets>bovis</ets>, ox.]</ety>
<fld>(O. Eng. Law.)</fld> <def>An oxgang, or as much land as an ox can
plow in a year; an ancient measure of land, of indefinite quantity, but
usually estimated at fifteen acres.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bovey coal</ent>⟦br⟧
